{
  "stem": "24111.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because before that day, only illegal immigrants arrived, which means people coming by night, you know, under the most difficult circumstance.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We came legally.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were immediately interned from the British in the camp of [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Athlit, ?] and we had to stay there three weeks in quarantine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that was an medical quarantine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was nothing, you know, nothing else.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, the end of Aron Menczer was not a good one.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Aron Menczer saved-- I don't want to say me-- he saved us all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His doing and his finding a way out, which [INAUDIBLE], also if you paid a lot of money, it was saving souls.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Aron Menczer very easily could have left Vienna, either with me or with later people, and who could-- have-- could have saved himself.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Aron Menczer never was a person like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because as long as he had one child under his supervision, he wouldn't leave that child.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It came to a day when the Germans-- when the Gestapo, eliminated the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with the last transport going to Poland and out to, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at that time, Theresienstadt, and from Theresienstadt they were sent to-- to the extermination camps, to-- He selected to go with the group, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and he went with the children.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Aron Menczer died in-- in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Today there is a monument in the only surviving Jewish temple in Vienna about Aron Menczer.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, a book was written.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The children died with him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Later on they found, written by children, all the number-- all the numbers I said-- all the names and birth dates and even addresses of the last group.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
